	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Thanks Jasmine for a very informative guide.  Wish there had been one when I was a young wizard.  I have a few additional items to offer.<BR>
<BR>
First, I agree with the 1hb directive.  There are more 1hb weapons in the game for casters than practically any other.  And hey, you may want to hold a mug in the other hand!  I prefer the WCS or Water Crystal Staff.<BR>
Second, get a complete set of Raw Silk from a tailor rather early on.  Upgrade to a Robe of the Keeper very soon above level 5 - I paid about 60pp on Bristlebane for mine (long long ago).<BR>
Third, get yourself a couple +2INT rings.  They're cheap.  +2INT Earrings are not to expensive either - raise that INT.  Makes you a mana battery!<BR>
Fourth, learn how to be a group maker.  Create an Assist button; assist the tank.<BR>
Fifth, be careful with AoE spells.  Use the AoE spells that do damage comparable with what your tank is doing - that way, you stand less chance of being aggroed.<BR>
Sixth, ping pong.  Hehe. Two casters in a group doing almost exactly the same damage with the foe going back and forth between them as they cast alternately.<BR>
Seventh, it takes forever to level on blues... I like killing yellows and reds.  It's possible if you use your brain; after all, you are supposed to be intelligent!<BR>
<BR>
Thanks again Jasmine!<BR>
Thaumaturge of Bristlebane<BR>
Dark Elven Wizard 30
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
